value: Dark pinkish buff terracotta, hand modelled and tooled. Faith sits on a rectangular slab. She has a bare feet, a long robe and a mantle draped over her head and arms, and down to ground at the back. Her right arm, lacking the hand, is raised, and her head and gaze are turned towards it. With her left hand she holds the top of a circular portrait medallion of Cardinal Lelio Falconieri in profile to the right. It is supported from below by a putto, who turns his head away from it and leans backwards. The figures rest on an oval base with concave curved sides. The back is roughly finished with daubs of clay and finger marks.
Bozzetto for the Monument to Cardinal Lelio Falconieri (d. 1648) in the tribuna of S.Giovanni dei Fiorentini, Rome
The contract for the monument to Falconnieri has not been found, but a date of c. 1665 seems likely
